com.camerontec.util.datamodel

Interface Decoder<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - source representation
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FIXFieldValueDecoder

    public interface Decoder<T>
    Interface for decoding from a source representation into data model types.

      • decodeDouble

        double decodeDouble(T source)
        Decode as a double.

        Warning: Java doubles are not precise representations and therefore may not be encoded as expected. Specifically, doubles should never be used for precise values like currency. Use java.math.BigDecimal instead.

        Parameters:
        source - The source representation.
        Returns:
        A double value.
        Throws:
        FieldException - If the specified source cannot be decoded to a double value.
